{
  "texts": [
    "Platforms have developed their own \"currencies or tokens\" (Syuhada et al. 2023), typically linked to a fiat exchange rate.",
    "This can be observed through currencies such as \"Linden dollars\" in Second Life, \"Mana\" in Decentraland, and \"Sand\" in Sandbox (Scarle et al. 2012; Nakavachara and Saengchote 2022; Li et al. 2023).",
    "Furthermore, these currencies or tokens are a relatively new concept, which is why research has focused on their efficiency, behavior, and associated risks (Zhang et al. 2022; Ghosh et al. 2023; Li et al. 2023; Qiao et al. 2023; Syuhada et al. 2023).",
    "The transition of certain tokens, such as Mana, has been observed to go from a period of market inefficiency in their early years to market efficiency; nevertheless, not all the tokens examined have produced identical outcomes (Zhang et al. 2022).",
    "Likewise, the hedging relationship between altcoins associated with the Metaverse and Bitcoin or other cryptocurrencies changes over time (Li et al. 2023; Qiao et al. 2023)."
  ]
}